modules.description: Provides functions for initializing, configuring, and managing network interfaces on Solo5 platforms, including packet transmission and reception. Operates with low-level network data structures such as Ethernet frames and IP packets. Used to enable network communication in unikernel applications running on Solo5-based systems.

Provides functions to manage Ethernet I/O, including writing packets with a specified size and header, listening for incoming packets, and disconnecting from the network device. Operates on network interface objects, MAC addresses, and packet buffers represented as Cstruct.t. Used to send and receive network traffic, monitor interface statistics, and configure network connections.
